<rules>
	<rule	Name="GetLastErrorMustBeCalledRightAfterPInvokeRule" 
		Type="Gendarme.Rules.Interoperability.GetLastErrorMustBeCalledRightAfterPInvokeRule, Gendarme.Rules.Interoperability, Version=@VERSION@, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null"
		Uri="" >
		<problem>GetLastError is called too late after the p/invoke call. It's possible it's value could have changed.</problem>
		<solution>Move the call to GetLastError just after the p/invoke call.</solution>
	</rule>
	<rule	Name="PInvokeShouldNotBeVisibleRule" 
		Type="Gendarme.Rules.Interoperability.PInvokeShouldNotBeVisibleRule, Gendarme.Rules.Interoperability, Version=@VERSION@, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null"
		Uri="" >
		<problem>P/Invoke methods should not be visible outside the assembly.</problem>
		<solution>Don't direcly export p/invoke. Wrap them in a class and provide adequate parameter validations.</solution>
	</rule>
	<rule	Name="UseManagedAlternativesToPInvokeRule" 
		Type="Gendarme.Rules.Interoperability.PInvokeShouldNotBeVisibleRule, Gendarme.Rules.Interoperability, Version=@VERSION@, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null"
		Uri="" >
		<problem>Method {0} contains a P/Invoke call that could be replaced with a managed call.</problem>
		<solution>Try to avoid p/invoke and replace this call with it's managed alternative.</solution>
	</rule>
</rules>
